# Image Naming Patterns & AI Generation Prompts

## Naming by Page Type

### Service page hero
```
[service]-[city].webp
boiler-service-peterborough.webp
emergency-plumber-peterborough.webp
gas-safety-certificate-peterborough.webp
```

### Service page secondary
```
[service]-[specific-action]-peterborough.webp
boiler-service-combustion-check-peterborough.webp
boiler-service-engineer-flue-inspection.webp
```

### Area page hero
```
plumber-[area-name]-peterborough.webp
plumber-werrington-peterborough.webp
plumber-orton-peterborough.webp
```

### Blog post images
```
[primary-keyword-slug]-[number].webp
how-to-bleed-radiator-step-1.webp
signs-boiler-needs-replacing-peterborough.webp
```

### Related service cards
```
[service]-service-peterborough-card.webp
central-heating-service-peterborough-card.webp
```

### OG / social share images
```
/public/images/og/[page-slug].jpg   ← JPG only for OG
/public/images/og/boiler-service.jpg
/public/images/og/emergency-plumber.jpg
```

## Alt Text by Image Type

### Hero (service pages)
"[Job description] by Gas Safe registered engineers in Peterborough"

### Hero (area pages)
"Local plumber carrying out [service] in [Area Name], Peterborough"

### Process / step images
"[Step description] during a boiler service in Peterborough"

### Team / trust images
"Gas Safe registered Peterborough Plumbers engineer in uniform"

### Blog images
"[Describes what image shows, matches article topic]"

### Related service cards
"[Service name] service being carried out in a Peterborough home"

### Decorative images
alt=""    ← empty string, not missing attribute

## AI Image Generation Prompts

### Required elements in every prompt
- Subject: What service is being performed
- Who: Plumber in navy uniform (not hi-vis unless outdoor/drainage)
- Environment: UK residential interior — modern or traditional British home
- Style: Photorealistic, professional, NOT stock photo aesthetic
- Lighting: Natural daylight from window OR warm interior lighting
- Quality: Sharp focus, clean composition, no watermarks
- Avoid: American-style kitchens, generic stock poses, Instagram lighting

### Boiler service
"A professional plumber in a navy uniform inspecting the controls of a white combi boiler mounted on a kitchen wall in a modern UK home. Natural light from a nearby window. Photorealistic. Sharp focus. Clean composition. No watermarks. British residential interior."

### Emergency plumber
"A plumber in a navy uniform crouched under a kitchen sink fixing a burst pipe, urgency conveyed through focused expression and tools on the floor. British kitchen interior. Photorealistic. Natural lighting."

### Gas safety certificate
"A Gas Safe registered engineer in a navy uniform holding a clipboard and inspecting a boiler, wearing ID badge. Modern UK home. Professional appearance. Photorealistic."

### Central heating
"A plumber fitting a chrome towel radiator to a bathroom wall in a UK home. Modern British bathroom. Photorealistic. Natural daylight."

### Area page hero
"Aerial or street-level photograph of [Area Name] residential neighbourhood in Peterborough, Cambridgeshire, UK. Suburban British homes. Overcast British daylight. No people."

### 3D service icons
"3D icon of a [boiler/wrench/pipe/radiator], isometric view, soft shadow, white background, clean modern style, muted navy and white colour palette."

### OG image prompt
"Professional services social media card, 1200x630px. Business: Peterborough Plumbers. Service: [Name]. Dark navy background, white and amber text. Service name large and centred, 'Peterborough' below, price bottom left, Gas Safe placeholder bottom right. Flat graphic design only. No watermarks."

## Logo & Favicon Standards

### Logo
- Primary: SVG (scales perfectly)
- Fallback: PNG at 2x (400×120px)
- Never use JPG for logos

### Favicon sizes
- /public/favicon.ico (32×32)
- /public/favicon-16x16.png
- /public/favicon-32x32.png
- /public/apple-touch-icon.png (180×180)
- /public/android-chrome-192x192.png
- /public/android-chrome-512x512.png
- /public/site.webmanifest

## Image Sitemap

Create `/public/image-sitemap.xml` with image entries for each service/area page. Add to robots.txt:
```
Sitemap: https://[domain]/sitemap.xml
Sitemap: https://[domain]/image-sitemap.xml
```

## AVIF Notes

Next.js serves AVIF automatically when source is WebP. Default config:
```js
images: { formats: ['image/avif', 'image/webp'] }
```
No extra config needed — just ensure source files are WebP.
